The paper deals with lower bounds on communication complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of read-once Boolean formulas suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The mention of randomized and quantum communication complexity suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG), as these are important concepts in the analysis of algorithms for learning. Finally, the paper's focus on depth-independent lower bounds suggests a connection to circuit complexity (cs.CC).
